name: PublicKey
comment: A public key. This interface contains no methods or constants. It merely serves to group (and provide type safety for) all public key interfaces. Note: The specialized public key interfaces extend this interface. See, for example, the DSAPublicKey interface in {@code java.security.interfaces}.

fields.name: serialVersionUID
fields.comment:
The class fingerprint that is set to indicate serialization
 compatibility with a previous version of the class.
